245
00:14:50,220 --> 00:14:53,240
But this is not done to Greek cities.

246
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:57,040
Do you understand? The Greeks
considered themselves special.

247
00:14:57,940 --> 00:15:00,600
And so, in 404 BCE,

248
00:15:00,940 --> 00:15:03,820
when Sparta defeated Athens
in the Peloponnesian War,

249
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:06,640
remember that Sparta did not do anything.

250
00:15:07,380 --> 00:15:11,120
Sparta just basically said, guys, will
you promise not to bother us again?

251
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:13,240
And Athens says, we promise. That was it.

252
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:17,220
Okay? So, what Alexander the Great did,

253
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,860
destroying Thebes, which

254
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:22,900
is one of the great cultural
centers of the Greek world,

255
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:25,240
that was like basically
setting off a nuclear bomb.

256
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:30,740
Okay? And from then on, the Greeks were
committed to overthrowing Alexander

257
00:15:30,740 --> 00:15:33,400
when the opportunity
arose. At the same time,

258
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:38,280
Alexander, by doing this,
by showing his ruthlessness,

259
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:41,040
he was able to, for now,

260
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:45,080
pacify all discontent.

261
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:46,540
People are now afraid of him.

262
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:48,060
And that's what Alexander wants.

263
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:50,560
He wants fear. Okay.

264
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:54,760
So, now that eternal
dissent has been pacified,

265
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:56,360
now that

